cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the design of LDPC codes, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses a reduction in complexity of the design procedure, which is a topic related to computational complexity. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper mentions the performance of the codes across different design rates, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the iterative decoding threshold and performance of the codes, which is a topic related to social and information networks. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a design method to obtain better QC-LDPC codes, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms.
